## Early game

**Zeugma** on Phobos (Dark Sector Survival) is among the best Rubedo spots at
any gear level — the wiki cites roughly 250 Rubedo per 5 minutes there, and
Phobos is one of Rubedo's two signature planets. Rubedo comes from containers
and lockers rather than enemy drop tables, so it's the mission's resource
density (not your squad's kill speed) that matters most here.

## Mid & late game

The wiki's general endgame advice is simply "run Void Survival or Defense" —
it cites over 1,000 Rubedo per 20 minutes from Orokin Void endless missions.
**Ani** (Survival, Steel Path) is a standard Void node for putting that into
practice with a squad. Since Rubedo comes from containers and lockers rather
than an enemy drop table, Resource Drop Boosters and the Steel Path passive
don't increase it — the longer the run, the more containers you clear.

